    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has browned, add your <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!), <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock</strong> to the pot and cook for 5 min further or until the onion has softened</p><p>Once softened, remove the pot from the heat and blitz until smooth with a <strong>(stick) blender</strong></p><p>Return the pot to a medium-high heat and cook for 2-3 min further or until the sauce begins to thicken – this is your <strong>Mexican-style adobo sauce</strong></p>",
